Is most of this even necessary?<p>Couldn&#x27;t you get away with:<p><pre><code>  function IV( $size, $ssl = false ) {
  	if ( $ssl && function_exists( &#x27;openssl_random_pseudo_bytes&#x27; ) ) {
  		return openssl_random_pseudo_bytes( $size, true );
  	}
  	return mcrypt_create_iv( $size, MCRYPT_DEV_URANDOM );
  }
</code></pre>
From the docs: <a href="http://it.php.net/manual/en/function.mcrypt-create-iv.php" rel="nofollow">http://it.php.net/manual/en/function.mcrypt-create-iv.php</a><p><pre><code>  5.3.0 MCRYPT_DEV_RANDOM and MCRYPT_DEV_URANDOM became available on Windows platforms.</code></pre>
